Class Sheet.Position

  • java.lang.Object
    • File.Sheet.Position
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Position
    Enclosing class:
    Sheet

    public class Sheet.Position
extends java.lang.Object
implements Position
    Inner class for Cell positions. The Position class holds a unique column and row index. Uniqueness is ensured by overriding the equals and hashCode methods.

    Cells can also be looked up by creating a new Position object with the same parameters. For example, to get the first cell, you could use the following code: 
     return cells.get(new Position(0, 0));
    Author:
    Jan-Willem Gmelig Meyling
